<TITLE> Garment workers end 13-hour roadblock </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 12 (bdnews24.com)  Workers of three garment factories Saturday took to the streets at Sheorapara in Mirpur demanding pay hikes and overtime payment. Angry workers of Outwear Ltd, Outright Ltd and Outfit Unit-2 blocked the road, halting traffic on Rokeya Sarani for more than 13 hours. They ended the road blockade at 9.30pm after they reached an agreement with factory owners at a meeting at the office of Bangladesh Garments Manufacturers and Exporters Association. The owners announced disbursement of salaries within the first seven workdays and overtime bills within the first 15 days of every month. They also signed a memorandum of understanding According to the MoU, if workers engage in activities such as road blockade over the demands disrupting movement of people and traffic, they will face legal action. Police, army officers and BGMEA leaders were present at the meeting. The protests trapped thousands of people in gridlock. Security was tightened in and around the area. Workers of Outright Ltd started the demonstration at 8:00am. Later the workers of the two other factories joined them. There were several attempts for negotiations between the workers and owners at the joint forces' Mirpur camp in the afternoon. Later, BGMEA leaders, garments owners and workers sat at a meeting at 6.10pm. The workers set a deadline for the owners to meet their demands one week ago but the owners did not listen to them, which forced them to take to the streets, workers alleged. bdnews24.com
